WLC_HANDLE_SET_USER_DATA(3)                              WLC CORE API FUNCTIONS

NAME

    wlc_handle_set_user_data - add user data to the handle

SYNOPSIS

    void wlc_handle_set_user_data(wlc_handle handle, const void *userdata);

DESCRIPTION

    wlc_handle_set_user_data() lets the programmer add arbitrary user data to
    the handle for later use or inspection.

RETURN VALUE

    None.

NOTES

    If the handle is invalid then wlc_handle_set_user_data() will do nothing.
    In order to validate that the user data was set one should use 
    wlc_handle_get_user_data(3).

ALSO SEE

    wlc_handle_get_user_data(3)
